==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{attention|ang}} {{term|ynce|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{attention|la}} {{term|uncia||twelfth part|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪntʃ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-inch.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪntʃ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# A unit of [[length]] equal to one-twelfth of a [[foot]] and equivalent to exactly 2.54 [[centimetre]]s.
# {{meteorology}} The amount of water which would cover a surface to the depth of an inch, used as a measurement of [[rainfall]].
# {{figuratively}} A very short distance.
#: ''"Don't move an '''inch'''!"''

